50|$|Weight gain can be {{a problem}} for some, with {{quetiapine}} causing more weight gain than fluphenazine, haloperidol, loxapine, molindone, olanzapine, pimozide, risperidone, thioridazine, thiothixene, trifluoperazine, and ziprasidone, but less than chlorpromazine, clozapine, <b>perphenazine,</b> and sertindole.|$|E
50|$|Amitriptyline/perphenazine (Duo-Vil, Etrafon, Triavil, Triptafen) is a {{formulation}} {{that contains}} the tricyclic antidepressant amitriptyline and the medium-potency typical (first-generation) antipsychotic, <b>perphenazine.</b> In the United States amitriptyline/perphenazine is marketed by Mylan Pharmaceuticals Inc. and Remedy Repack Inc.|$|E
